Serves 2 with leftovers but just adjust fish quantity to suit
There are 3 parts to this: salsa, rice, fish (400g piece of firm white fish)
/////
Salsa:
  (If you have a food processor just add everything together at once)
    Grind the following with a mortar and pestle:
          About half a cup toasted pumpkin seeds
          2* cloves of garlic
    Add the following:
          Finely diced 1* red pepper
          Finely diced 2* tomatoes
          A bunch of finely chopped fresh coriander
          A teaspoon of dried chilli flakes
          Finely diced fresh red / green / jalapeno chilli
          A teaspoon ground coriander
          A teaspoon ground cumin
          A teaspoon paprika
          Juice and zest from 1-2 limes
          Juice of half a lemon
          Some salt 
/////
Fish:
  Slice:
          400g (or more or less) firm white fish into 4 pieces
  Put in a bowl and add half of the salsa so the fish is covered
  Leave to marinade while starting the rice
  Pre-heat oven to 200Â°C
  Prepare a tray, line it with baking paper
/////
Rice:
  Using a pot with a lid
    Heat a little oil and add:
          Diced brown onion
    Fry gently until onion is soft
    Then add:
          A teaspoon ground coriander
          A teapoon ground cumin  
          Small handfull of slivered almonds / pinenuts / chopped pistachios if you want
          Lime zest
    Fry gently for a couple of mins or until nice and toasted through
    Add:
          1 cup of rice and stir so it's coated
    Add:
          2 cups of chicken stock
    Bring to boil then cover, turn heat really low, set timer for 12 minutes
    After 12 minutes take off the heat completely and set timer for 12 minutes again
/////
Bringing it together:
  The oven should be hot now
  Put fish on tray with the marinade salsa
  Bake for 12 minutes (i.e. same timer)
  Fish should be cooked through and crisp on edges
  Arrange fish on top of rice and add any tray juices
  Top with the remaining salsa and more lime juice
